Hundreds of mourners are currently in Ijebu-Igbo area of Ogun State for the burial of Late Senator Buruji Kashamu. Kashamu died of COVID-19 complications on Saturday. DAILY POST learnt that his remains were brought into Ijebu-Igbo from Lagos last night. On Sunday morning, people from all walks of life defied the COVID-19 weekend lockdown in Ogun State as they thronged the residence of the late chieftain of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), who they described as a philanthropist. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-826642 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/kashamu-3-360x360-1.jpg" alt="" width="360" height="360" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/kashamu-3-360x360-1.jpg 360w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/kashamu-3-360x360-1-300x300.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/kashamu-3-360x360-1-150x150.jpg 150w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/kashamu-3-360x360-1-80x80.jpg 80w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/kashamu-3-360x360-1-45x45.jpg 45w" sizes="(max-width: 360px) 100vw, 360px">  Many could not control their tears as they wailed when Kashamuâ€™s remains were being lifted from the vehicle. Watch the video: